article.headline: McNeese St. 26, Nicholls 17
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. -- Andre Anderson scored two touchdowns in McNeese State's 26-17 win over Nicholls State on Saturday. Anderson capped off McNeese State's 13-play, 82-yard opening drive with a 4-yard touchdown run. He then scored again, this time from 3 yards out, on McNeese State's opening drive of the third quarter to help the Cowboys retake the lead, 14-10. Cody Stroud connected with Kegan Myers later in the quarter to give McNeese State (4-5, 3-3 Southland Conference) a 24-10 lead. Nicholls State (1-8, 0-5) attempted to rally, drawing within seven points with only 1:56 to play, but Everett Ellefsen sacked LaQuintin Caston in the end zone on the Colonels' final possession. Caston paced Nicholls State, throwing for 92 yards on 14-of-21 passing and added 129 rushing yards on 27 carries. The win snaps a four-game McNeese State losing streak and improves the Cowboys series record to 25-11.
